@@aHISTORY@@W

The cleric tradition descends from the five-office priesthood of the Solar
Court of the Undivided Disk, whose Dawn Liturgists and Seal College priests
maintained the cosmological machinery that kept the Black Sun Shard dormant
beneath the Great Pyramid. As the Solar Court fractured after the Ninth
Meridian Catastrophe, surviving covenant-keepers fled the desert and sought
alignment with the civic institutions of the crossroads cities. The Violet
Compact era gave them formal standing: clerics became the civic-sanctioned
channel for divine covenant, their rites documented under registry supervision
and their shrines positioned at watched squares within city walls. The tradition
holds that faith is not sentiment but infrastructure — a binding that holds the
world's deeper catastrophes at bay, and must be maintained with the same
precision the Keepers once applied to water and shadow.

@@aCLERIC@@W

Clerics are keepers of sacred covenant, shaping divine force through faith and
rite. They stand between ruin and renewal, turning conviction into miracles.

@@aPassive class abilities@@W
  * @@wSpell Critical Damage@@W (unlocked at mortal level 20): increases
    spell critical multiplier by @@w2 x Wisdom@@W.

@@aUnique Cleric mechanics@@W
  * Prime mortal attribute is @@wWisdom@@W.
  * Excels at high-impact spell spikes when criticals land, making Cleric a
    strong base for holy and support-caster progressions.

@@aCleric reincarnation bonuses@@W
